---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { profile } from '../data/profile';
---

<BaseLayout title="CV">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Curriculum Vitae</p>
    <h1>Short Web CV</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This page provides a brief academic self-introduction, including my
      education, research experience, academic activities, honors, and
      technical background. A PDF version of my CV is also available for
      reference.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Profile</h2>
      <p>
        I am a undergraduate student at Jilin University
        preparing for graduate study in physics and quantum information.
      </p>
      <p>
        My current academic interests include statistical physics, quantum
        information, high energy physics, Bell inequalities, multipartite
        quantum correlations, and open quantum systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a class="button-link" href={profile.cv.pdfPath} download>
          Download PDF CV
        </a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <div class="stack">
        <div>
          <p>
            <strong>Jilin University</strong><br />
            B.Eng. in Traffic and Transportation<br />
            College of Transportation<br />
            September 1, 2021 - June 30, 2026
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Current Status: Undergraduate</li>
            <li>GPA: 85.98/100</li>
            <li>TOEFL: 98</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Selected Core Curriculum</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Quantum Mechanics: 95.4</li>
            <li>Classical Electrodynamics: 93</li>
            <li>Thermodynamics and Statistical Physics: 84.6</li>
            <li>Methods of Mathematical Physics: 94</li>
            <li>University Physics: 97</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Research Experience</h2>
      <div class="stack">
        <div>
          <h3>Nuclear Matter Phase Structure Study</h3>
          <p class="meta">
            Institute of Modern Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences<br />
            June 2023 - August 2023<br />
            Supervisor: Hao Qiu
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Research Topic:</strong> Collective polarization of nuclear
            matter in the RHIC energy region, phase boundaries, and critical
            points.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Studied introductory topics related to the phase structure of
              nuclear matter, including quark confinement, quark-gluon plasma,
              and critical behavior in complex phase transitions.
            </li>
            <li>
              Developed a preliminary understanding of hypernucleus
              reconstruction and attempted basic modeling using CERN ROOT.
            </li>
            <li>
              Learned and used CERN ROOT for data analysis and modeling
              practice.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>
            Quantum Nonlocality and Multipartite Entanglement in (3,2,2)
            Scenarios
          </h3>
          <p class="meta">
            University of Tokyo<br />
            July 2025 - Present<br />
            Supervisors: Prof. Naomichi Hatano; Jaeha Lee
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Research Topic:</strong> Bell-type inequalities, including
            Mermin and Svetlichny inequalities, in multipartite quantum
            systems, focusing on biseparable and genuinely multipartite
            entangled states.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Investigated the structure of biseparable states in the (3,2,2)
              Bell scenario and their relation to bipartite extensions.
            </li>
            <li>
              Conducted Monte Carlo simulations to analyze distributions in the
              (M,S) operator plane.
            </li>
            <li>
              Studied GHZ- and W-class genuinely multipartite entangled states
              through optimized measurement settings and Svetlichny-type
              inequalities.
            </li>
            <li>
              Analyzed robustness to white noise through critical visibility.
            </li>
            <li>
              Developed reproducible Python codes using NumPy, SciPy, CVXPY,
              and Matplotlib for quantum-correlation simulations,
              violation-region analysis, and SDP-based boundary tests.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Academic Activities</h2>
      <div class="stack">
        <div>
          <h3>Fudan International Summer School for Graduate Students on Optics</h3>
          <p class="meta">August 2024</p>
          <p>
            Topics: Nanophotonics, nonlinear and ultrafast optics, quantum
            optics, and quantum computing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Physics of Open Systems: Resonance, Symmetry and Topology</h3>
          <p class="meta">August 2025</p>
          <p>
            Topics: Open systems, resonance dynamics, non-Hermitian physics,
            and Floquet topological systems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Awards and Honors</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Expected: Jilin University Second-class Scholarship<br />
          Awarding Institution: Jilin University<br />
          Date Received: 2026
        </li>
        <li>
          Provincial Second Prize in the National College Students Mathematical
          Contest in Modeling<br />
          Awarding Institution: Chinese Society of Industrial and Applied
          Mathematics<br />
          Date Received: December 2023
        </li>
        <li>
          University-level Second Prize of China Undergraduate Physics
          Tournament<br />
          Awarding Institution: College of Physics, Jilin University<br />
          Date Received: December 2022
        </li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Technologies</h2>
      <div class="card-grid two-column">
        <div>
          <h3>Programming Languages</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Python</li>
            <li>C++</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Tools and Technologies</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>CERN ROOT</li>
            <li>MATLAB</li>
            <li>CVXPY</li>
            <li>NumPy</li>
            <li>SciPy</li>
            <li>Matplotlib</li>
            <li>LaTeX</li>
            <li>SolidWorks</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
